Description: Different functions includes constructing composite indicators, imputing missing data, and evaluating imputation techniques. Additionally, different tools for data normalization. Detailed methodologies of  'Indicator' package are: OECD/European Union/EC-JRC (2008), 'Handbook on Constructing Composite Indicators: Methodology and User Guide', OECD Publishing, Paris, <DOI:10.1787/533411815016>, Matteo Mazziotta & Adriano Pareto, (2018) 'Measuring Well-Being Over Time: The Adjusted Mazziottaâ€“Pareto Index Versus Other Non-compensatory Indices' <DOI:10.1007/s11205-017-1577-5> and De Muro P., Mazziotta M., Pareto A. (2011), 'Composite Indices  of Development and Poverty: An Application to MDGs' <DOI:10.1007/s11205-010-9727-z>.
